    Type: QuantityValue

    A simple quantity, e.g. 2cm

    URI: nmdc:QuantityValue

    schema:QuantityValue

    Parents

    • is_a: AttributeValue - The value for any value of a attribute for a sample. This object can hold both the un-normalized atomic value and the structured value

    Attributes

    Own

    • quantity value➞has numeric value OPT
      • Description: The number part of the quantity
      • range: Double
    • quantity value➞has raw value OPT
      • Description: Unnormalized atomic string representation, should in syntax {number} {unit}
      • range: String
    • quantity value➞has unit OPT
      • Description: The unit of the quantity
      • range: Unit

    Inherited from functional annotation:

    • functional annotation➞was generated by OPT
      • Description: provenance for the annotation. Note to be consistent with the rest of the NMDC schema we use the PROV annotation model, rather than GPAD
      • range: Activity
    • functional annotation➞subject OPT
      • range: GeneProduct
    • functional annotation➞has function OPT
      • range: FunctionalAnnotationTerm

    Domain for slot:

    • quantity value➞has numeric value OPT
      • Description: The number part of the quantity
      • range: Double
    • quantity value➞has raw value OPT
      • Description: Unnormalized atomic string representation, should in syntax {number} {unit}
      • range: String
    • quantity value➞has unit OPT
      • Description: The unit of the quantity
      • range: Unit
